did.unittitle: Department of Astronomy, Yale University, records

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of correspondence, observation books, memoranda, and research notes documenting the activities and operations of the Yale Department of Astronomy. Included are subject files maintained by the directors of the Yale Observatory.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 14-B (YRG 14-B), Records of academic departments and programs of the Yale Faculty of Arts and Sciences.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Department of Astronomy, Yale University, Records (RU 274). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

altformavail.head: Existence and Location of Copies
altformavail.p: The papers of Frank Schlesinger from both Yale University and the University of Pittsburgh are available on microfilm (Film MISC 978).

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged as follows: I. Hubert Anson Newton, ca. 1860-1929. II. William Lewis Elkin, ca. 1883-1935. III. Ernest William Brown, 1880-1939. IV. Frank Schlesinger, 1915-1952. V. Dirk Brouwer, 1939-1967. VI. Astronomical Journal, 1941-1969. VII. Association of Universities for Research in Astronomy (AURA), 1965-1972. VIII. Research Data, 1874-1962. IX. Financial Records, 1882-1959; and subsequent accessions.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of correspondence, observation books, memoranda, and research notes documenting the activities and operations of the Yale Department of Astronomy. Included are subject files maintained by the directors of the Yale Observatory.
